## Step 0.9: Design Scope Detection

Automatically detect feature scope from Basic Design + SRS content.
Scope determines which phases (FDD/API/BDD) to execute.

**WHY**: Many real-world features are backend-only. Running FDD for them wastes
context and produces irrelevant documents. Scope detection prevents this.

### 0.9.1: Load BD + SRS Content

Read BOTH BD + SRS (SRS provides additional scope context via use cases and actors).

```pseudo
# CONSTRUCT: File paths from feature_dir (set in Step 0.8)
bd_file = f"documents/features/{feature_dir}/{feature}-BASE-basic-design.md"
srs_file = f"documents/features/{feature_dir}/{feature}-BASE-srs.md"

# LOAD: Both documents
bd_content = read_file(bd_file)
srs_content = read_file(srs_file)  # May not exist for some features
combined_content = bd_content + (srs_content or "")
```

### 0.9.2: Detect Scope Indicators

**Matching**: Case-insensitive substring search. Multi-word phrases reduce false positives.

```pseudo
# INDICATORS: Case-insensitive, multi-word phrases
frontend_indicators = ["screen", "ui component", "react", "page layout", "form",
                       "bff", "navigation", "frontend module", "user interface"]
backend_indicators = ["service layer", "repository", "entity", "controller",
                      "database", "batch job", "message queue", "worker", "backend module"]

# SCAN: Count meaningful occurrences
fe_count = count_case_insensitive(combined_content, frontend_indicators)
be_count = count_case_insensitive(combined_content, backend_indicators)

# DETERMINE: Scope based on indicator presence
if fe_count > 0 and be_count > 0:
    detected_scope = "fullstack"
elif fe_count > 0 and be_count == 0:
    detected_scope = "frontend"
elif be_count > 0 and fe_count == 0:
    detected_scope = "backend"
else:
    # EDGE CASE: No indicators found → default to fullstack (safest)
    detected_scope = "fullstack"
    display("⚠️ No clear scope indicators found in BD/SRS. Defaulting to fullstack.")
```

### 0.9.3: Auto-detect API Contracts Need (frontend/fullstack only)

```pseudo
api_indicators = ["api endpoint", "rest api", "bff", "api contract", "http method"]
needs_api_contracts = (detected_scope != "backend") and
                      count_case_insensitive(bd_content, api_indicators) > 0
```

### 0.9.4: Confirm with User

```pseudo
AskUserQuestion:
  question: "Scope detected from BD+SRS analysis. Confirm or override?"
  header: "Scope"
  options:
    1. label: "Confirm: {detected_scope}"
       description: "FE: {fe_count} indicators, BE: {be_count} indicators"
    2. label: "Override: backend"
       description: "BDD only — no frontend documents"
    3. label: "Override: frontend"
       description: "FDD + optional API Contracts — no backend documents"
    4. label: "Override: fullstack"
       description: "FDD + API Contracts + BDD — all documents"

DESIGN_SCOPE = user_choice  # "backend" | "frontend" | "fullstack"
```

### 0.9.5: Display Scope Execution Plan

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
📋 DESIGN SCOPE: {DESIGN_SCOPE}
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```

| DESIGN_SCOPE | Phase 1 (FDD) | Phase 2 (API) | Phase 3 (BDD) |
|-------------|---------------|---------------|---------------|
| backend     | Skip          | Skip          | Run           |
| frontend    | Run           | {auto-detect} | Skip          |
| fullstack   | Run           | Run           | Run           |

**IMPORTANT**: DESIGN_SCOPE applies to ALL sub-features.
Do NOT re-detect scope per sub-feature. See Sub-Feature Processing section.

---

## Variable Reference for Remaining Workflow

The following variables were determined in previous steps. The AI executing this
workflow must carry these forward to all subsequent phases:

| Variable | Set In | Values | Used In |
|----------|--------|--------|---------|
| DESIGN_SCOPE | Step 0.9 | "backend" / "frontend" / "fullstack" | Phase 1, 2, 3, Sub-Features, Completion |
| needs_api_contracts | Step 0.9.3 | true / false | Phase 2 |
| CREATE_BASE | Step 0.8 | true / false | Sub-Features |
| HAS_SUBFEATURES | Step 0.8 | true / false | Sub-Features |
| use_abc_pattern | Phase 1 (A+B+C) | true / false | Phase 1 FDD structure |
| DD_RAG_DESIGNS | Step 0.6 | array (existing DD patterns from design layer) | Phase 1, 2, 3 per-agent context |
| DD_RAG_CODE | Step 0.6 | array (code patterns from code layer) | Phase 1, 2, 3 per-agent context |
| DD_RAG_SPECIALISTS | Step 0.6 | array (matched specialist filenames) | Phase 1, 3 per-agent context |

**CRITICAL**: These are AI-tracked variables (not shell environment variables).
When a scope guard says `if DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend"`, this means: "If the user
confirmed backend scope in Step 0.9, skip this phase."

---

## Phase 1: Frontend Detail Design

**Scope Guard**: Skip if DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend"

```pseudo
if DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend":
    display("⏭️ Phase 1: Skipped (backend scope — no FDD)")
    # Proceed directly to Phase 3
else:
    # A+B+C check (see A+B+C FDD Pattern section below)
    if HAS_SUBFEATURES and sub_feature_count >= 4:
        use_abc_pattern = true
    else:
        use_abc_pattern = false
```

### Step 1.1: Read Agent Specification
```bash
# Load FDD orchestrator via specialist-load
node core/cli/ops.js specialist-load --type document --category detail-design-frontend --name _orchestrator
FDD_SPEC=$(node -e "const r=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('cache/ops-result.json','utf8')); console.log(r.data?.content || '')")
# Contains: 10 micro-agent references, JIT loading pattern, validation rules
```

### Step 1.2: Load Context
```pseudo
evidence_content = read_file(evidence_file)
basic_design_content = read_file(bd_file)
```

### Step 1.3: Direct Agent Execution (NO orchestrator)

frontend-detail-specialist.md IS the orchestrator instructions. AI reads the agent spec
and executes its workflow directly. There is NO orchestrate-fdd.js file — this is
direct agent execution (confirmed: backend-design-specialist.md line 6).

### Step 1.4: Generate Sections with JIT Loading (10 micro-agents)

| # | Agent File | Section |
|---|------------|---------|
| 0 | fdd-00-document-info.md | Document information |
| 1 | fdd-01-overview.md | Overview |
| 2 | fdd-02-business-flow.md | Business flow |
| 3 | fdd-03-screens.md | Screen specifications |
| 4 | fdd-04-state.md | State management |
| 5 | fdd-05-data-integration.md | Data integration |
| 6 | fdd-06-error.md | Error handling |
| 7 | fdd-07-responsive.md | Responsive design |
| 8 | fdd-08-performance.md | Performance |
| 9 | fdd-09-visual-design.md | Visual design |

**Per-Section Enrichment (for each micro-agent):**

**1.4.1 Architecture Analysis (component/module sections)**

For component-level sections (fdd-03 screens, fdd-04 state, fdd-05 data-integration), invoke the **architecture-analyzer** skill:
- Detect duplicate components against existing frontend codebase
- Validate proposed component architecture against project tech stack

**1.4.2 Pattern Analysis**

After loading each micro-agent specialist, invoke the **pattern-analyzer** skill:
- Check proposed patterns against specialist recommendations
- Use alignment results to guide section generation

**1.4.3 Design Validation (Per Section)**

After generating each section, invoke the **design-validator** skill:
- Q1: Evidence grounding — design decisions trace to evidence
- Q2: ID uniqueness — no duplicate IDs
- Q3: Bilingual ratio — within 60:40 to 80:20
- Q4: Interface purity — no implementation code in design doc
- If any violation: fix before proceeding to next micro-agent

### Step 1.5: Quality Validation
```pseudo
validation_result = node.run(".claude/utils/tests/fdd-validator.js", [document_path])
if validation_result.exit_code != 0:
    display("⚠️ Frontend DD validation warnings:")
    display(validation_result.stdout)
```

### Step 1.6: Write Frontend DD
```pseudo
frontend_dd_file = f"documents/features/{feature_dir}/{feature}-BASE-frontend-detail-design.md"
write_file(frontend_dd_file, frontend_dd_content)
display(f"✅ Created: {frontend_dd_file}")
```

### FDD Enforcement Mode (TodoWrite + Checkpoints)

**WHY**: FDD has 10 micro-agents executed sequentially. Without enforcement, AI may skip
agents or lose context mid-generation.

**Before Phase 1** — Initialize:
```pseudo
TodoWrite([
    { content: "FDD Section 0: Document Info", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 1: Overview", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 2: Business Flow", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 3: Screens", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 4: State Management", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 5: Data Integration", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 6: Error Handling", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 7: Responsive Design", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 8: Performance", status: "pending" },
    { content: "FDD Section 9: Visual Design", status: "pending" },
])
```

**For EACH micro-agent (0-9)**:
```pseudo
TodoWrite: mark section N as in_progress
```bash
# Load FDD section N specialist
node core/cli/ops.js specialist-load --type document --category detail-design-frontend --name fdd-0N-{section}
FDD_SECTION_SPEC=$(node -e "const r=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('cache/ops-result.json','utf8')); console.log(r.data?.content || '')")
```

# RAG: Per-agent context injection (non-blocking)
try:
    agent_graph = await rag.getGraphContext({ name: f"fdd-{N:02d}" })
    FDD_KW_MAP = { 3: "screen", 4: "state-management", 5: "api-client",
                   6: "error-handling", 8: "performance", 9: "visual-design" }
    if N in FDD_KW_MAP:
        section_specialists = await rag.querySpecialists(
            [FDD_KW_MAP[N], STACK_FRONTEND_FRAMEWORK], topK=2)
    else:
        section_specialists = []
except:
    agent_graph = None; section_specialists = []

# Generate section content with RAG context:
#   DD_RAG_DESIGNS (existing patterns) + DD_RAG_CODE (code patterns)
#   + agent_graph (entity relationships) + section_specialists (specialist patterns)
validation = node.run(".claude/hooks/validate-section.js", [document_path, N])
if validation.exit_code != 0:
    display(f"⚠️ Section {N} failed — regenerating (max 2 retries)")
write_file(f".checkpoints/fdd-s{N}.lock", f"Section {N} complete at {timestamp}")
TodoWrite: mark section N as completed
```

**After all 10** — Verify:
```pseudo
checkpoint_count = count_files(".checkpoints/fdd-s*.lock")
if checkpoint_count != 10:
    display(f"❌ FDD enforcement failed: {checkpoint_count}/10")
    STOP
display("✅ FDD enforcement passed: 10/10 checkpoints")
```

