## Phase 2: API Contracts

**Scope Guard**: Skip if DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend"
**Auto-detect**: If DESIGN_SCOPE == "frontend", check needs_api_contracts from Step 0.9.3

```pseudo
if DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend":
    display("⏭️ Phase 2: Skipped (backend scope)")
elif DESIGN_SCOPE == "frontend" and not needs_api_contracts:
    display("⏭️ Phase 2: Skipped (no API indicators in BD)")
else:
    # RAG: Load existing API patterns (non-blocking)
    try:
        api_patterns = await rag.findByStereotype("Controller", { topK: 3 })
        api_arch = await rag.queryWithArchitecture(
            "api endpoints rest controller dto",
            { stereotype: "Controller", topK: 3 }
        )
    except:
        api_patterns = []; api_arch = []

    Step 2.1: Derive from Frontend DD (+ RAG api_patterns as reference)
        # Screen data needs → GET endpoints
        # User actions → POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints
        # State mutations → Request/Response DTOs

    Step 2.2: Generate API Contracts document
        # Use api_arch for naming conventions and DTO structure consistency

    Step 2.3: Write API Contracts
        api_file = f"documents/features/{feature_dir}/{feature}-BASE-api-contracts.md"
        write_file(api_file, api_contracts_content)
        display(f"✅ Created: {api_file}")
```

**NO enforcement** — single-step derivation, not multi-agent process.

---

## Phase 3: Backend Detail Design

**Scope Guard**: Skip if DESIGN_SCOPE == "frontend"

**WHY**: BDD runs last in fullstack scope because backend implements API contracts derived
from frontend needs (frontend-first approach). In backend-only scope, BDD loads BD + SRS
directly instead of FDD + API Contracts.

```pseudo
if DESIGN_SCOPE == "frontend":
    display("⏭️ Phase 3: Skipped (frontend scope — no BDD)")
```

### Step 3.1: Read Agent Specification
```bash
# Load BDD orchestrator via specialist-load
node core/cli/ops.js specialist-load --type document --category detail-design-backend --name _orchestrator
BDD_SPEC=$(node -e "const r=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('cache/ops-result.json','utf8')); console.log(r.data?.content || '')")
# Type: Direct Micro-Agent Workflow (No Orchestrator)
# 10 micro-agents, 3-layer enforcement, JIT loading
```

### Step 3.2: Load Context (scope-dependent)
```pseudo
if DESIGN_SCOPE == "fullstack":
    fdd_content = read_file(fdd_file)
    api_content = read_file(api_contracts_file)
    context_source = "FDD + API Contracts"
elif DESIGN_SCOPE == "backend":
    bd_content = read_file(bd_file)
    srs_content = read_file(srs_file)
    context_source = "BD + SRS (no frontend documents)"
```

### Step 3.3: Direct Agent Execution (NO orchestrator)

backend-design-specialist.md IS the orchestrator instructions. AI reads agent spec
then loads micro-agents via JIT. orchestrate-bdd.js DOES NOT EXIST.

### Step 3.4: Generate Sections with JIT Loading (10 micro-agents)

| # | Agent File | Section |
|---|------------|---------|
| 0 | bdd-00-document-info.md | Document information |
| 1 | bdd-01-service-overview.md | Service overview |
| 2 | bdd-02-business-logic.md | Business logic |
| 3 | bdd-03-api-endpoints.md | API endpoints |
| 4 | bdd-04-data-database.md | Data & database |
| 5 | bdd-05-integration.md | Integration |
| 6 | bdd-06-error-handling.md | Error handling |
| 7 | bdd-07-performance.md | Performance |
| 8 | bdd-08-security.md | Security |
| 9 | bdd-09-test-cases.md | Test cases |

**Per-Section Enrichment (for each micro-agent):**

**3.4.1 Architecture Analysis (component/module sections)**

For component-level sections (bdd-03 API endpoints, bdd-04 data/database, bdd-05 integration), invoke the **architecture-analyzer** skill:
- Detect duplicate services/repositories against existing backend codebase
- Validate proposed service architecture against project tech stack

**3.4.2 Pattern Analysis**

After loading each micro-agent specialist, invoke the **pattern-analyzer** skill:
- Check proposed patterns against specialist recommendations
- Use alignment results to guide section generation

**3.4.3 Design Validation (Per Section)**

After generating each section, invoke the **design-validator** skill:
- Q1: Evidence grounding — design decisions trace to evidence
- Q2: ID uniqueness — no duplicate IDs
- Q3: Bilingual ratio — within 60:40 to 80:20
- Q4: Interface purity — no implementation code in design doc
- If any violation: fix before proceeding to next micro-agent

### Step 3.5: Quality Validation
```pseudo
validation_result = node.run(".claude/utils/tests/bdd-validator.js", [document_path])
if validation_result.exit_code != 0:
    display("⚠️ Backend DD validation warnings:")
    display(validation_result.stdout)
```

### Step 3.6: Write Backend DD
```pseudo
backend_dd_file = f"documents/features/{feature_dir}/{feature}-BASE-backend-detail-design.md"
write_file(backend_dd_file, backend_dd_content)
display(f"✅ Created: {backend_dd_file}")
```

### Step 3.7: Insert DD-SECTION Markers (Auto-Split Enablement)

**WHY**: DD-SECTION markers enable `/plan` auto-split for large DDs (> 300 lines).
Without markers, the pseudo-code generator falls back to single-file mode (F1).

```pseudo
bdd_lines = backend_dd_content.split("\n").length

if bdd_lines > 300:
    # Insert DD-SECTION markers around each micro-agent section group
    # Markers use HTML comments so they don't affect rendering
    # Section IDs should be descriptive, lowercase with hyphens
    #
    # Example markers (adapt to actual BDD structure):
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION: core-logic -->
    #   ## 1. Service Overview
    #   ## 2. Business Logic
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION-END: core-logic -->
    #
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION: api-data -->
    #   ## 3. API Endpoints
    #   ## 4. Data & Database
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION-END: api-data -->
    #
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION: integration -->
    #   ## 5. Integration
    #   ## 6. Error Handling
    #   ## 7. Performance
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION-END: integration -->
    #
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION: security-testing -->
    #   ## 8. Security
    #   ## 9. Test Cases
    #   <!-- DD-SECTION-END: security-testing -->
    #
    # Rules:
    #   - Section ID = any [\w][\w-]* string (section-agnostic, E23)
    #   - Group related BDD sections (2-3 per marker) for balanced sub-plans
    #   - Place markers BEFORE first heading and AFTER last heading in group
    #   - Missing DD-SECTION-END is tolerated (auto-closed at next start or EOF)
    display(f"📂 BDD {bdd_lines} lines > 300 — insert DD-SECTION markers for auto-split")
else:
    display(f"📄 BDD {bdd_lines} lines ≤ 300 — no markers needed (single-file mode)")
```

### BDD Enforcement Mode (3-Layer: Hooks + TodoWrite + Checkpoints)

**WHY**: BDD has 10 micro-agents and is the longest generation phase.
backend-design-specialist.md (v3.0) was designed with 3-layer enforcement built-in.

**Before Phase 3** — Initialize:
```pseudo
mkdir -p .checkpoints
rm -f .checkpoints/bdd-s*.lock

TodoWrite([
    { content: "BDD Section 0: Document Info", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 1: Service Overview", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 2: Business Logic", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 3: API Endpoints", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 4: Data & Database", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 5: Integration", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 6: Error Handling", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 7: Performance", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 8: Security", status: "pending" },
    { content: "BDD Section 9: Test Cases", status: "pending" },
])
```

**For EACH micro-agent (0-9)**:
```pseudo
# Layer 1 (Hooks): Validate previous section
if N > 0:
    node.run(".claude/hooks/validate-section.js", [document_path, N-1])

# Layer 2 (TodoWrite): Mark in_progress
TodoWrite: mark section N as in_progress

# Generate: Load micro-agent (JIT) → generate content
```bash
# Load BDD section N specialist
node core/cli/ops.js specialist-load --type document --category detail-design-backend --name bdd-0N-{section}
BDD_SECTION_SPEC=$(node -e "const r=JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('cache/ops-result.json','utf8')); console.log(r.data?.content || '')")
```

# CALI: Context-Aware Layer Injection (non-blocking)
# Maps BDD sections to code stereotypes for pattern retrieval
CALI_MAP = { 1: "Service", 2: "Service", 3: "Controller",
             4: "Repository", 5: "Service", 6: "Service",
             7: "Service", 8: "Service", 9: "Service" }
try:
    if N in CALI_MAP:
        similar = await rag.retrieveSimilarPatterns(
            CALI_MAP[N], feature_module,
            { limit: 3, minConfidence: 0.7, includeCode: true }
        )
        # Inject actual code patterns from similar stereotypes into agent context
    agent_graph = await rag.getGraphContext({ name: f"bdd-{N:02d}" })
except:
    similar = { patterns: [], source: "error" }
    agent_graph = None

# Generate section with: agent instructions + DD_RAG_CODE + similar.patterns + agent_graph

# Layer 1 (Hooks): Validate current section
node.run(".claude/hooks/validate-section.js", [document_path, N])

# Layer 3 (Checkpoints): Write lock file
write_file(f".checkpoints/bdd-s{N}.lock", f"Section {N} complete at {timestamp}")

# Layer 2 (TodoWrite): Mark completed
TodoWrite: mark section N as completed
```

**After all 10** — Final verification:
```pseudo
checkpoint_count = count_files(".checkpoints/bdd-s*.lock")
if checkpoint_count != 10:
    display(f"❌ BDD enforcement failed: {checkpoint_count}/10")
    STOP
display("✅ BDD enforcement passed: 10/10 checkpoints")
```

### Final Design Validation (FDD + BDD)

After all FDD and BDD sections are generated, invoke the **design-validator** skill on each complete document:
- Run Q1-Q4 on the entire FDD document
- Run Q1-Q4 on the entire BDD document
- Verify cross-document consistency (API contracts match between FDD and BDD)
- If violations found: iterate on affected sections
- If all pass: Continue to Sub-Feature Processing / Write

---

## Sub-Feature Processing

**Scope applies to ALL sub-features** — detect once for BASE, apply to all.

**WHY**: Evidence from real-world projects shows 100% of features with sub-features have the same
scope across all subs. Re-detecting per sub would waste context and create inconsistency.

```pseudo
if CREATE_BASE:
    1. Create BASE documents first (scope-dependent: 1-3 files)
    2. For each sub-feature: Repeat Phase 1/2/3 with SAME DESIGN_SCOPE

if not CREATE_BASE and HAS_SUBFEATURES:
    1. For each sub-feature: Repeat Phase 1/2/3 with SAME DESIGN_SCOPE

For each sub-feature:
    - Use SAME DESIGN_SCOPE (do NOT re-run Step 0.9)
    - Use SAME needs_api_contracts flag
    - Add Service Boundaries section (cross-sub-feature interfaces)
```

---

## Pseudo-code Generation

**WHY**: Pseudo-code is consumed by `/plan` to create implementation plans.
PseudoCodeGenerator transforms human-readable DD into LLM-optimized format.

**Scope-adapted rule**: Generate pseudo-code for EVERY DD that was created in this run.
PseudoCodeGenerator requires an existing DD file path (`humanDDPath, srsPath, docType`).
It cannot generate from BD+SRS — skip missing DDs instead of failing.

```pseudo
srs_file = find("documents/features/{feature_dir}/*-srs.md")

# FDD pseudo-code (only if FDD document exists)
fdd_file = find("documents/features/{feature_dir}/*-frontend-detail-design.md")
if fdd_file exists:
    fdd_content = readFileSync(fdd_file, "utf8")
    fdd_pseudo = PseudoCodeGenerator(fdd_file, srs_file, "FRONTEND_DD")

    # Size-based trigger: markers + > 300 lines → multi-file
    if fdd_content.includes("<!-- DD-SECTION:") AND fdd_content.split("\n").length > 300:
        fdd_pseudo.setSplitMode("multi-file")
        result = await fdd_pseudo.generateAndSplit()
        masterPath = fdd_file.replace(".md", ".pseudo")
        writeFileSync(masterPath, result.master)
        display("✅ Frontend pseudo-code (multi-file master): {masterPath}")
        for [sectionId, content] in result.sections:
            sectionPath = fdd_file.replace(".md", "-{sectionId}.pseudo")
            writeFileSync(sectionPath, content)
            display("   Section: {sectionId}.pseudo")
    else:
        fdd_pseudo.save(fdd_file.replace(".md", ".pseudo"))
        display("✅ Frontend pseudo-code (single): {pseudo_path}")
else:
    display("⏭️ Frontend pseudo-code: Skipped (no FDD document)")

# BDD pseudo-code (only if BDD document exists)
bdd_file = find("documents/features/{feature_dir}/*-backend-detail-design.md")
if bdd_file exists:
    bdd_content = readFileSync(bdd_file, "utf8")
    bdd_pseudo = PseudoCodeGenerator(bdd_file, srs_file, "BACKEND_DD")

    # Size-based trigger (C7): markers + > 300 lines → multi-file
    if bdd_content.includes("<!-- DD-SECTION:") AND bdd_content.split("\n").length > 300:
        bdd_pseudo.setSplitMode("multi-file")
        result = await bdd_pseudo.generateAndSplit()
        # Save master
        masterPath = bdd_file.replace(".md", ".pseudo")
        writeFileSync(masterPath, result.master)
        display("✅ Backend pseudo-code (multi-file master): {masterPath}")
        # Save section files
        for [sectionId, content] in result.sections:
            sectionPath = bdd_file.replace(".md", "-{sectionId}.pseudo")
            writeFileSync(sectionPath, content)
            display("   Section: {sectionId}.pseudo")
    else:
        # Fallback: single file (backward compat)
        bdd_pseudo.save(bdd_file.replace(".md", ".pseudo"))
        display("✅ Backend pseudo-code (single): {pseudo_path}")
else:
    display("⏭️ Backend pseudo-code: Skipped (no BDD document)")

# Validate (non-blocking — report but don't stop)
for each pseudo_file:
    report = PseudoCodeValidator(pseudo_file, dd_file, srs_file)
    report.save(context_dir)
```

| DESIGN_SCOPE | FDD Pseudo | BDD Pseudo |
|-------------|------------|------------|
| backend     | Skip       | Generate   |
| frontend    | Generate   | Skip       |
| fullstack   | Generate   | Generate   |

---

## Post-Generation: RAG Index & Graph Update

**WHY**: Indexing generated DD into RAG enables future features to learn from this design.
Graph extraction creates entity relationships for architecture compliance checks.
This is the feedback loop that makes RAG progressively smarter with each feature.

```pseudo
# Index generated DD into RAG + extract graph entities (non-blocking)
try:
    rag = HippoRAGService.getInstance(feature, branch)

    if fdd_content:
        await rag.indexContent(fdd_content, "fdd", "DD_COMPLETE")
        await rag.extractAndUpdate(fdd_content, "fdd", "frontend-detail-design")
        display("📊 FDD indexed into RAG (design layer)")

    if bdd_content:
        await rag.indexContent(bdd_content, "bdd", "DD_COMPLETE")
        await rag.extractAndUpdate(bdd_content, "bdd", "backend-detail-design")
        display("📊 BDD indexed into RAG (design layer)")

    if api_content:
        await rag.indexContent(api_content, "fdd", "DD_COMPLETE")
        display("📊 API Contracts indexed into RAG (design layer)")

    display("✅ RAG updated: DD documents indexed for future reference")
except:
    display("⚠️ RAG indexing skipped (non-blocking)")
```

| DESIGN_SCOPE | FDD Index | BDD Index | API Index |
|-------------|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| backend     | —         | Index     | —         |
| frontend    | Index     | —         | If exists |
| fullstack   | Index     | Index     | Index     |

**Non-blocking**: Indexing failures do not affect the DD output or state update.

